dd6\ud83c\udffe\u200d\u2640\ufe0f\ud83e\uddfd\ud83e\udee7\u2728\ud83d\udc95We can\u2019t pour from a empty cup can we? Day in my life... Morning Routine... Cleaning... Laundry.\n#selfcareroutine #blackmomsofinstagram #cleanhome #organizedhome #asmr", "timestamp": "2026-07-01T01:42:41.000Z", "videoDuration": 102.12, "videoPlayCount": 2366682, "videoViewCount": 881724, "likesCount": 150127, "commentsCount": 2822, "displayUrl": "https://scontent-sjc6-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/730223339_18061996877757515_7432063032006845229_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-sjc6-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=111&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gF3zVq6wjVNXOtGMNh4FwI_0EUUvcgLIK8GMYiLBR71CdgAmpyEBVfF4A7CPu66Wa4&_nc_ohc=O7NjrnTqWDsQ7kNvwGv0hXY&_nc_gid=RRYDuq4tAxGEGjt9tNgDwA&edm=ADp7STQBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AQBDNofYTRdCZbj3CBLBAumRYVuMJ8xZyavdMlTpdO3LVQ&oe=6A61C3CA&_nc_sid=c6f216", "videoUrl": "https://scontent-lga3-2.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m86/AQNz2GK3_UC-8sChwqiogJwyVmIdSqG8bBRBIl5_sgdUrZbZ555lR9cJDQm4MUSYnUUBl08NrY8JX5AfTB-WqpahJv29wI4O1Pv2-R0.mp4?_nc_cat=100&_nc_sid=5e9851&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=WT-wI4P44vYQ7kNvwETe09g&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6Inhwdl9wcm9ncmVzc2l2ZS5JTlNUQUdSQU0uQ0xJUFMuQzMuNzIwLmRhc2hfYmFzZWxpbmVfMV92MSIsInhwdl9hc3NldF9pZCI6MTYzOTAyMjE5MDUxMTIxMywiYXNzZXRfYWdlX2RheXMiOjE3LCJ2aV91c2VjYXNlX2lkIjoxMDA5OSwiZHVyYXRpb25fcyI6MTAyLCJ1cmxnZW5fc291cmNlIjoid3d3In0%3D&ccb=17-1&vs=44fcb73fa1fdaf50&_nc_&_nc_gid=Vh-FaAyz4UrKGsqUvObjLA&_nc_ss=7c689&_nc_zt=28&oh=00_AQDMlpURH8BZM_xMpZzqJOFrdqmUOM-8iEq_WaBRb9z62Q&oe=6A5DAA55", "musicInfo": {"artist_name": "operation_niki", "song_name": "Original audio", "uses_original_audio": true, "should_mute_audio": false, "should_mute_audio_reason": "", "audio_id": "27563671949985116"}, "ownerUsername": "operation_niki", "ownerFullName": "Rochelle N. Stewart", "transcript": "I read so many of your comments saying, I'm exhausted watching this, or this is way too much, is this all a show? And honestly, I get it. When you see everything squeezed into a minute, it looks like I'm trying to be productive every second of the day, but that's not really what's happening here. This isn't about perfection. It's not about trying to earn my worth by checking off a list. It's simply the way I take care of myself and my home before the day gets too busy. If you know me in real life, you know this has always been me. Since I was a child, I learned from my grandmother very early on that when you look good, you feel good, and that definitely manifests physically. Drinking water, brushing my teeth, washing my face, doing my skincare, those aren't extra tasks for me. They're just part of getting ready. Making my bed isn't because it has to be perfect, it's because I love walking back into my room that feels peaceful later, and it helps to keep me productive. Clearing off my nightstand takes about 30 seconds. Lighting a candle makes my home feel nice and cozy. I know y'all know about aromatherapy. Starting a load of laundry takes less than a minute, and while it's washing, I'm free to move on with my day. None of these things feel stressful to me because they're habits now. I don't think about them, I just do them. And the best part? They actually reduce my stress. I don't spend the rest of the day staring at an unmade bed, piles of laundry, or clutter thinking, I'll just get to that later. No, this routine isn't for everyone, and that's okay. You don't have to wake up like I do to have a good morning. We all recharge differently. But for me, this isn't overwhelming, it's grounding. It's how I create peace before the responsibilities of the day happen. I am a wife and a mom of three, so that does matter. And if there's one thing I hope people take away from my videos, it's not that you should do everything I do, it's that you should find a routine that brings peace to you."}, {"shortCode": "DaJNbahR6oW", "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DaJNbahR6oW/", "caption": "Sometimes the only quiet moment I get is at th